    "Subsequently, Wang et al. (2023b) showed that RETRO at sizes up to 9.5 billion parameters largely outperforms GPT on specific knowledge-intensive tasks.",
    "Furthermore, Wang et al. (2023a) illustrated that when scaled up to 48 billion parameters and instructiontuned, RETRO performed better than equivalent GPT models on several question answering, reading comprehension and summarization tasks.",
    "In this paper we continue the exploration of RETRO versus GPT through the lens of parameter efficient finetuning.",
    "We apply P-tuning, Adapter modules and LoRA to multiple tasks with retrieval for both RETRO and GPT models.",
    "To our knowledge, this paper provides the first in-depth comparison of various Parameter Efficient Fine-Tuning integrated with Retrieval-Augmented Generation, uniquely applied to both GPT and RETRO models."
